Disable FlashAttention-3 (Hopper) build in sgl-kernel for DGX Spark GB10.

MAINAHEAD VARIANT — regenerated against SGLang tag v0.5.14.

Why a separate file from sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch:
  Upstream restructured the FA3 enablement between v0.5.13 and v0.5.14. The old
  recipe dead-coded an UNCONDITIONAL `if ("${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL
  "12.4")` block that force-set SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 ON. That line no longer
  exists. v0.5.14 (sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt ~line 108) now ships:

      set(DEFAULT_SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 OFF)
      if (... aarch64|arm64 ...) message("For aarch64, disable FA3 by default")
      if (CUDA >= 12.4 AND NOT aarch64) set(DEFAULT_SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 ON)
      ...
      option(SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 "Enable FA3" ${DEFAULT_SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3})

  i.e. upstream ALREADY defaults FA3 OFF on aarch64. On our GB10 (aarch64) fleet
  the canonical patch is therefore REDUNDANT — FA3 is off out of the box. This
  variant keeps the build pipeline uniform (same APPLY_SGL_KERNEL_DISABLE_FA3
  gate + the 'dgxarley sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch' marker grep) and adds
  belt-and-suspenders by wrapping the only DEFAULT-ON setter (the non-aarch64
  path) in `if (FALSE AND ...)`, so SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 stays OFF on EVERY
  arch this recipe is ever built on — not just aarch64. The downstream
  `if (SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3)` build block (~line 393) and the sm_90a gencode
  block (~line 233) then skip all ~475 hopper/instantiations/flash_fwd_*.cu
  files and the sm_90a cubins.

Selected automatically by build_sm121_image.sh when the recipe sets
SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1 (installed under the canonical name
sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch). The v0.5.13 recipes keep the original.

Apply to: sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt, AFTER sgl-kernel-arch-prune.patch (arch-prune
edits lines ~136/~217, below this hunk, so there is no interaction).

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.14

diff --git a/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt b/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
index df8be77..5e20ddd 100644
--- a/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/sgl-kernel/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -109,7 +109,12 @@ set(DEFAULT_SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 OFF)
 if (CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR MATCHES "^(aarch64|arm64)$")
     message(STATUS "For aarch64, disable FA3 by default")
 endif()
-if ("${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "12.4" AND NOT CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR MATCHES "^(aarch64|arm64)$")
+# dgxarley sgl-kernel-disable-fa3.patch: FA3 is Hopper-only (SM90a) and can
+# never run on GB10 (SM121). v0.5.14 already defaults FA3 OFF on aarch64; this
+# wraps the only DEFAULT-ON setter (non-aarch64 path) in `FALSE AND ...` so the
+# option() default stays OFF on EVERY arch and the FA3 build block + sm_90a
+# gencode are skipped entirely. Structure kept byte-identical for easy diffing.
+if (FALSE AND "${CUDA_VERSION}" VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL "12.4" AND NOT CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR MATCHES "^(aarch64|arm64)$")
     set(DEFAULT_SGL_KERNEL_ENABLE_FA3 ON)
 endif()
 
